SABC Chairperson Bongumusa Makhathini has promised to beef up the SABC's security measures. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - SABC Chairperson Bongumusa Makhathini, says the public broadcaster's investigations are resulting in push-back from those who are implicated. He was speaking during the Fix show about the assassination attempt on Thami Zikode on Friday night. Makhathini promised to beef up the SABC's security measures. WATCH: Former SABC employee takes stand at state capture The public broadcaster said Zikode was followed home from Auckland Park last night. The motive for the attack is not yet known. Zikode is currently working on a forensic investigation into fraud at the cash-strapped broadcaster. Karima sifted through the Sunday papers with Veteran Journalist and Broadcaster John Perlman as well as Senior Political Reporter at eye witness news, Theto Mahlakoana. #Dstv403